To add this overlay to a Gentoo system, run the following command:

layman -o https://raw.github.com/ryao/pipelight-overlay/master/overlay.xml -f -a pipelight

Note that you must have both dev-vcs/git and app-portage/layman installed on
your system for this to work.

Installation of pipelight requires keywording a few packages and configuring a new category. An example follows:

echo cross-i686-w64-mingw32 >> /etc/portage/categories

mkdir -p /etc/portage/package.keywords
echo 'app-emulation/wine-compholio ~*' >> /etc/portage/package.keywords/pipelight-overlay
echo 'cross-i686-w64-mingw32/gcc ~*' >> /etc/portage/package.keywords/pipelight-overlay
echo 'cross-i686-w64-mingw32/binutils ~*' >> /etc/portage/package.keywords/pipelight-overlay
echo 'cross-i686-w64-mingw32/mingw64-runtime ~*' >> /etc/portage/package.keywords/pipelight-overlay
echo '=www-plugin/pipelight-9999 **' >> /etc/portage/package.keywords/pipelight-overlay

emerge =www-plugin/pipelight-9999
